        <updateDate>2021-12-02T20:39:50Z</updateDate>
        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><b>Truth in Healthcare Marketing Act of 202</b><strong>1</strong></p> <p>This bill prohibits as an unfair or deceptive trade practice a person from misrepresenting (1) whether the person holds a state health care license; or (2) the person's education, training, degree, license, or clinical expertise. </p> <p>A person's advertisement for the person's health care services must disclose the license under which the person is authorized to provide those services. </p> <p> <p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
